01:28:00,114 --> 01:28:04,076
Well, you guys'll be able to see.
I-I gotta take off right now.

906
01:28:06,370 --> 01:28:09,457
I'm almost afraid to look.

907
01:28:09,540 --> 01:28:11,292
- Drink it.
- Right.

908
01:28:11,375 --> 01:28:13,794
Hurry up.

909
01:28:15,045 --> 01:28:18,257
The water main doesn't run under the house.

910
01:28:21,385 --> 01:28:23,596
Well, I know that now.

911
01:28:25,222 --> 01:28:28,559
Shit, Tom.

912
01:28:34,857 --> 01:28:36,984
Argh!

913
01:28:38,694 --> 01:28:41,572
Get him on the rug.

914
01:28:47,119 --> 01:28:49,622
- Don't look at him. Roll him over.
- Yeah.

915
01:28:49,705 --> 01:28:52,416
Let's go! All right,...

916
01:28:52,500 --> 01:28:54,794
...get outta the way.

917
01:30:35,352 --> 01:30:37,438
Tom?

918
01:30:41,942 --> 01:30:44,487
Are you here?

919
01:30:51,243 --> 01:30:53,329
Shit!

920
01:30:54,830 --> 01:30:56,457
Argh!

921
01:30:59,210 --> 01:31:02,171
Out of the way, Kurt!

922
01:31:04,006 --> 01:31:05,007
Arghh!

923
01:31:25,986 --> 01:31:30,741
They were gonna kill you, Tommy.
You and Maggie both.

924
01:31:36,831 --> 01:31:40,376
- Are you OK?
- Yeah.

925
01:31:52,513 --> 01:31:55,307
Cold-blooded murder.

926
01:31:56,767 --> 01:31:59,728
I can't let something like that happen.

927
01:32:00,771 --> 01:32:03,149
Not here.

928
01:32:04,191 --> 01:32:07,278
This was a decent neighbourhood.

929
01:32:19,457 --> 01:32:23,419
If I ever feel the light again

930
01:32:24,253 --> 01:32:27,339
Shining down on me

931
01:32:28,799 --> 01:32:31,761
I don't have to tell you

932
01:32:32,636 --> 01:32:35,765
How welcome it would be

933
01:32:36,849 --> 01:32:39,393
I felt the light before

934
01:32:39,477 --> 01:32:42,855
But I let it slip away

935
01:32:44,315 --> 01:32:51,864
And I just keep on believing
that it'll come back some day

936
01:32:52,364 --> 01:32:54,825
It's not the spotlight

937
